cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a space-efficient, probabilistic data structure designed for set reconciliation in distributed systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper introduces a new way of populating bloom filters and unique bloom filter mappings between peers. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper discusses bandwidth-efficient set reconciliation in networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the eventual consistency of states between nodes in a system. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the accuracy and false positive rate of the distributed bloom filter.
